        "cooked": "<p>I have Signal, on a Mac running macOS 11.7.10 (Big Sur). Sometimes, I turn on Do Not Disturb mode to disable the notifications for all my apps, if I want to focus on something.</p>\n<p>When Do Not Disturb is on, I don‚Äôt see any notifications from Signal (as expected), but I still hear that ‚Äúpop‚Äù sound, which I think is distracting. Is there any way to make Signal disable the sound when Do Not Disturb is on?</p>",
